description:
Job Description:

Support service through hot line and email;
Gather preliminary information and pass to second line support;
Understand customer requirement, provide solution through usage of ITIS software package;
Write up of customer requirement;
Conduct system testing;
Provide user training;
Prepare and maintain user documentation, such as user manual, training manual, etc.

Job Requirement:

With 2 year or above relevant experience;
Diploma or equivalent is a plus;
Knowledge in logistics, freight forwarding, and transportation is a plus;
Experience in using ERP systems of any kind is a plus;
Responsive, good communication/interpersonal skills, and open to new tasks/ exposure;
Able to listen to customers and understand their key concerns in order to achieve better services and solutions (with analytical mindset);
Patient, helpful, eager to help customer resolving issues relating to services offered;
Good command of spoken & written English and/or Chinese.

Employees with good performance will be promoted.



We are equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates.

Job Highlights:

5-day work, overtime payment and shift allowance;
Able to work flexibility working hour;
Fresh graduate welcome;

Job Responsibilities:

Perform project management for the corporate clients with all in house and non-in-house activities, monitor page turn, assure quality and deliver the documents to client on the timely basis;
Communicate and cooperation in a close working relationship between clients and the internal departments;

 Job Requirements:

University graduates in any discipline;
2 years of working experience in customer service, administration or financial printing will be an advantaged;
Fluent in both written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Ability to work effectively in a team environment;
Mature, self-motivated and good communication skills to deal with corporate clients, investment bankers and lawyers;
Able to work under pressure and meet tight deadline;
Required to work shift duties with shift allowance;
Willing to work overtime;
Applicants with less experience will be considered as Customer Service Assistant;
Fresh graduate is also welcome;

We offer an attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate.

To apply, please send your full resume and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".
(Personal data provided will be used for recruitment purpose only)

Handling in-store and e-commerce customer enquiries and complaints via all communication channels, including but not limited to email, live chat, telephone and face-to-face; including products’ promotion, logistics, products return;
Support the team in sales activities, including order processing and post-sales coordination;
Responsible for in-store e-commerce work station operations, including maintain the e-commerce system, handle in-store pickup orders and provide excellent customer service at store.
Responsible for the administration support including data input and coupon/GWP redemption;
Responsible for Customer Service reports;
Assist in handling ad-hoc assignments if needed.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above;
1 year relevant experience from customer service field would be an advantage;
Detail-minded, positive and proactive working attitude, with strong customer service mindset;
Good command of both spoken & written English and Mandarin;
Shift duty is required;
NO sales target need to be achieved;
Fresh graduate is also welcome to apply;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as senior position.

We offer:

6.5 days off per month
17 Public Holidays
11 Annual Leave
Attendance bonus
Shift allowance
Medical benefits

We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Please apply in strict confidence by sending personal resume together with salary expected and date availability by email: careers @ harveynichols. com .hk or Whatsapp 9828-0637.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates.  Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only.  Candidates not notified within eight weeks may consider their application unsuccessful.  All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months.  A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request by contacting our Human Resources Division.

Post-secondary or above, with relevant experience gained from customer service centre or call centre is an advantage;
Answer in-bound calls and escalate the customer requests to the related parties by prompt action
Prepare weekly report and assist in daily routine clerical works;
Cheerful, pleasant, polite, patient and able to work independently;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Able to communicate in English and Mandarin is preferred; and
Shift duty is required
Please send your full detailed resume with expected salary and date available to The Human Resources Manager, NEC Hong Kong Limited, 25th Floor, The Metropolis Tower, 10 Metropolis Drive, Hunghom, Kowloon or by e-mail.


Personal data provided by job applicant will be used strictly in accordance with employer's personal data policy, a copy of which will be provided immediately upon request.

Responsibilities: 

Deliver highest level customer service and maintain good relationship with the customers in a professional manner;
Develop potential customers;
Cooperate with other teams and team members to ensure timely resolution of customer requests, problems and documenting actions.
Arrange customer appointments;
Handle and follow-up on customer cases & sample;
Perform ad hoc projects as assigned by manager.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above;
1-2 years related experience in Customer Service/Sales/Admin is a plus;
Experience in pregnancy & maternity services and products, medical fields are preferred;
Good command of spoken Mandarin, Cantonese and English;
Proficient in computer skills, e.g. Microsoft Office, English and Chinese typing;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Mature with a positive attitude, aggressive, self-motivated and strong desire to deliver exceptional results with great attention to accuracy and details;
Fresh graduates & IANG holders are welcomed;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Customer Service Assistant.

Major Responsibilities:

Responsible for providing quality customer service to the Company clients from HK and China market;
Coordinate with cross-department counterparts to enhance operation efficiency and customer experience.
Establish good relationship with clients
Handle incoming telephone calls/Enquiry from electronic platform and greet visitors in a professional and courteous manner;
Handling account opening and margin financing procedures;

 Qualifications & Requirements:

Degree Holder with major in Business, Finance or related disciplines;
1 year of relevant experience in the similar position preferably;
Holder of SFC Type 1 License is preferred;
Tactful customer services skills and good problem solving abilities;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Good written and spoken English and Chinese, with excellent command of Putonghua

We are looking for a high caliber candidate to develop his/her career in our Company：

The Job :

To handle customers' enquiries, orders and complaints in an efficient and professional manner;
To manage parts order processing, and monitor backlog status and parts delivery;
To follow up with customers for invoicing and payment arrangement;
To analyze GM% and freight cost of sales orders so as to improve the profitability;
To liaise with central service team for pricing and lead time checking;
To act as key user for Internal Service Program and solve the issues raised by service technicians (training will be provided);
To drive and grow parts sales by actively contacting customers and identifying their needs;
To support the service jobs schedule and maintenance service team;
To provide feedback on the efficiency of customer service process;
Ad-hoc projects assigned by line Manager.

The Person:

Degree in Business Administration or equivalent;
Min. 2 years relevant experience in customer service or sales administration. Proven track record in order processing；
Independent, fast learner, self-motivated, details-minded, well organized and able to work under pressure;
Business acumen and Customer-oriented;
Good interpersonal and negotiation skills;
Good command of spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Knowledge in SAP will be an advantage;
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

We offer competitive remuneration package and generous fringe benefits including 5-days work week, medical and dental insurance, discretionary bonus and excellent working condition. Interested candidates please apply through JobsDB.

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only for employment-related purpose.

Responsibilities:

Liaise with overseas customers in order confirmation and handle their daily enquiries;
Communicate with China factories and internal parties;
Ensure accurate and on-time production orders, order status reports and delivery time schedule, etc;
Coordinate samples development and delivery on time and prepare for customer presentation;
Follow up the whole merchandising process from product development until production;
Prepare product related documents and reports;
Handle ad hoc assignments as required.

Requirements:

High diploma or above in Sales and Marketing or related discipline;
Minimum 2 years experience of merchandising or manufacturing trading in TOYS ;
Familiar with US & EU market will be advantage;
Strong interpersonal and time management skill;
Well-organized, self-motivated, flexible and able to work independently;
Good PC skill (MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint & Chinese WP is essential);
Immediate available is preferred.

Attractive salary package will be offered to the right candidates. 

Interested parties. Please send your full resume including current and expected salary by clicking “Apply Now”.   Personal data will be collected for recruitment purpose only.

Learn us more at www.winfun.com
